## Result

The Artificial Neural Network (ANN) model was successfully trained on the student dataset to predict future career paths using multi-class classification.

The dataset was preprocessed by handling missing values, encoding categorical features using one-hot encoding, and scaling the input features. The model was trained using the Keras framework with multiple dense layers and softmax activation for classification.

After training, the model achieved satisfactory performance on the test dataset. The evaluation metrics such as accuracy, precision, recall, and F1-score indicate that the model is capable of learning patterns from the data and making reasonable predictions.

The confusion matrix shows that the model correctly classifies a significant number of instances, although some misclassifications occur due to the complexity of multiple career categories.

Overall, the ANN model demonstrates the effectiveness of machine learning techniques in predicting student career outcomes based on their academic background and skill set.
